22/08/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- Chief of Staff Admiral Panayotis Hinofotis has resigned in order to run as a candidate in the September 16th snap elections. He will seek a seat in parliament on the ruling New Democracy (ND) party ticket, the Naftemporiki daily reported on Tuesday (August 21st). According to the newspaper, the Hellenic Navy General Staff chief, Vice-Admiral Dimitrios Grapsas, will succeed Hinofotis. (Nafthemporiki, Adezmevtos tipos, Avriani - 22/08/07; Focus, Kathimerini - 21/08/07)
